0.2.12

	- New Inli theme
	- Add figure element support
	- Some bugfix

0.2.11

	- PowerTip updated
	- Elements added or modified with tooltip-* classes are now handled
	- Add font-sans-serif, font-serif and font-monospace
	- H1 to H6 titles are more polished
	- Automatic text-indent removed, .indent class added

0.2.10

	- The TipSwift javascript library is replaced by the awesome PowerTip library
	- Add some examples on test pages

0.2.9

	- Add some missing -*-border-radius and correct some values
	- All default fonts are now open source fonts
	- Fix the input type button on the inline form display
	- Padding for tiny buttons is reduced from 8px to 5px
	- Some cleanups

0.2.8

	- Fix the dropdown-side-menu height
	- The Komuneco organization is the new official owner of the Aquarelle project
	- Rewriting dropdown-top-menu and dropdown-side-menu
	- All default fonts are now open-source
	- Some little fixes on buttons

0.2.7

	- Add the ability to give all button styles to anchors elements
	- Add a dark version of the default theme
	- Add a new « bubble mode » to display hover-dropdown-list and focus-dropdown-list

0.2.6

	- Add a NEWS file to have a simple history of our developments
	- Some bugfix

0.2.5

	- Add highlight classes for tables
	- Add develoment tools to test pages
	- Some bugfix

0.2.4

	- Replace the dropdown-top-menu-* and dropdown-side-menu-* old classes by the new dropdown-menu-*
	- Remove the depth limitation for top menus and side menus
	- Some bugfix

0.2.3

	- Add development tools when dev.aquarelle.min.js is loaded instead of aquarelle.min.js
	- Add README file
	- Some bugfix

0.2.2

	- Aquarelle's CSS can now be fully loaded in one call
	- Add IAB support
	- Add the .noindent typographic trick
	- Add test files
	- Tipsy plugin replaced by its fork TipSwift
	- Some bugfix

0.2.1

	- Add SOURCE file
	- First default fontface becomes Arial instead of Verdana

0.2.0

	- First stable version of Aquarelle
